15," Sure, here are some steps you can take to help protect your computer and personal information from malware:

1. Install anti-virus software: Install reputable anti-virus software that can detect and remove malware from your computer. Make sure to keep the software up to date with the latest virus definitions.
2. Keep your operating system and software up to date: Regularly update your operating system and other software to ensure you have the latest security patches and features.
3. Be cautious when downloading and installing software: Only download software from reputable sources, and read user reviews and ratings before installing. Be wary of free software, as it may come with malware.
4. Use strong passwords and keep them private: Use unique and complex passwords for all of your accounts, and avoid sharing them with anyone.
5. Use two-factor authentication: Enable two-factor authentication (2FA) on your accounts to add an extra layer of security. This requires you to provide a second form of verification, such as a code sent to your phone or a biometric scan, in addition to your password.
6. Back up your data: Regularly back up your important data",0
